        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 1 at 4:00PM EDT until July 1 at 4:15PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located over Alplaus, or
near Scotia, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Schenectady, Clifton Park, Rotterdam, Amsterdam, Scotia, Glenville,
Niskayuna, Hagaman, Rotterdam Junction, Alplaus, East Glenville,
Burnt Hills, Pattersonville-Rotterdam Junction, Country Knolls,
Charlton, Princetown, Glenridge, Hoffmans, Harding Crossing, and
Gifford.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
